<br>
Ok I am starting the diologue on our Raiding rules and guidelines.  This is a living document - I will change and add to it extensivly.  I know that Arielyn, Horro and Pensfan all have some great stuff to input as well as many others.<br>
<br>
RL = Raid Leader<br>
GL = Group Leader<br>
MA = Main assist <br>
MT = Main Tank<br>
AT = Alternate Tank<br>
SA = Secondary Assist<br>
ML = Master Looter<br>
MP = Main Peeler (non standard term - most just call it peeler)<br>
<br>
- RL is IN CHARGE<br>
<br>
- RL gives directions - don't take it personal but follow it!<br>
<br>
- ASSIST MA - ASSIST MA - ASSIST MA! sometimes the MA and MT are ussualy the same person but it might be differant and often is the puller. So sometimes even the MT has to have an assist hotkey <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  But when a Main Assist has been determined - stick with it. If you don't stay on the same target as the MA you will break mez/ gain aggro and this is bad.  Makes it hard on the healers and will lose your enchanter/necro/bard (they either quit thru frustration or get killed) if you keep breaking mez.<br>
<br>
- Tank Mez = there are un mezable/un slowable / un rootable (depends) targets; so often there needs to be a designated person to get aggro and hold aggro for the target that must be meleed away from main group.  Often a pet can be used as a tank mezzer of varying success.<br>
<br>
- MA is the only person Melee and nukers will assist and choose targets with unless directed otherwise by the RL. Also depends on when Nukes/ and Debuffs are allowed to be cast.  Sure there are PLENTY of times that the RL might not be able to keep up with all action so feel free to do on the spot crowd control if needed<br>
<br>
- Crowd control:  Most well done pulls should only give us 1 to 2 adds if any.  Crowd control is a tricky game.  Make sure that if you are in an area that has high probability of adds that you understand the crowd control plan.  One enchanter might not be enough to do all on their own - Pet classes will use pets to tank mez when needed.  Roots and slows can be cast while the chanters (if any)  can get around to landing mezzes.  There are some amazing things that can be done with good crowd control.<br>
<br>
-AT - Alternate tank - this is the designated tank to tank mez an add.  Heck any melee MIGHT turn into the designated AT after a death.  There may be more available but unless the AT has aggro issues or there are more than 1 non mez / root adds prolly won't designate.  The AT is the designated hitter to take aggro if necessary.  If there is no Adds then the AT just fights with the group and takes aggro if needed (MT down / healers LOM)<br>
<br>
- SA is Ussually the AT BUT there are times when he may not be.  The SA is a common person that the RL will call on to tank mez a target.  The Reason for an SA is that Nukers and defuffers will need to have a quick target ready to target the 2nd mob in line.  Depending on whether the Add summons will determine how much the support classes can take care of the add before the main battle moves to the add.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Regardless if a SA is put to work you can be sure that he will be targeted on the next mob to fight.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
- Main Peeler needs to be designated. The MP is commonly a Ranger, Pally, or Shadow Knight due to their taunting hit rate combined with their Spell line - Beast Lord could do this very well too depending on pet control.  The MP is the one the RL will call to Peel the an enraged target off of a caster.  If the Wiz, druid, sham or cleric gets aggro they are probably going to need a peeler to save them.  Necro, mage and enchanters can ussually either Mez or pet tank their aggroed Mob- maybe a shaman could do this too.  If you can't get a root off on the aggroed mob -casters - please go near the fighting so the MP can find you.  Regardless - THE MP will either go when called or will do it on his own if the Aggroed caster is in his group.  ANY GL can call for the Peeler as the RL will not have a good view of all action all the times and may not pick up on a fast aggroed MOb.  Heck any caster that gains aggro can announce it to the raid channel as soon as they get aggroed. If you wait to announce it - you may be dead.  WHEN ANNOUNCED - ONLY THE MP goes to gain aggro.  Unless RL calls otherwise MP goes all else stay on may target - if even more than 1 person leaves the main target - you might get a wipepout.  Depending on zone you might need more than one of these.<br>
<br>
- Grouping arrangement will be decided by the RL you might not think it is the way you would do it - but be sure, the RL has a reason for setting it up that way.<br>
<br>
- You might not get exp ONCE during raid. You might lose exp overall during the raid.  Raids are for items that are not likely to be obtained thru single group arrangements.<br>
<br>
- sign into raid channel even if your current graphic settings can't allow you to read the messages (BTW if this is a problem - it can be fixed by changing your color settings and you can also change your font size to make it easier to read - all this is explained in your eq manuel supplimant on your hardrive) This allows the RL to track players on the raid.<br>
<br>
- Kiting - we in TF use kiting against adds more than other guilds and players.  This a great tactic for a player to hold aggro and kite the mob in circles around the group until it can be handled.  There will be times where this will work.  Then in some dungeons we will just not have the manueverability to pull this off.  Watch for instructions on this - depending on zone.<br>
<br>
- Even tho raids are demanding and sometimes emotional for folks - they are Hella fun - I enjoy going on raids even when I know that I will get poor exp and the drops will not be for me. Sooner or later the raid that we go on will benefit your class. For example I went on a raid into TOFS and while lots of blades drop there - it is mostly stuff good for youngling players/alts vs the folks that can raid there.  There are some great caster items that drop there; But that place is a blast and it turns out that there was a good helmet I ended up getting from there after all.<br>
