- all no drop are rolled on by interested players on drop<br>
- All droppable are collected by ML per group and worthwhile drops are given to RL to hold.  This goes for a jewels and stuff too.<br>
<br>
- at end of the raid all (good) items held by RL are rolled on in one of a couple formats <br>
<br>
* one roll by all players and they take their pick from the top<br>
* NBG rolls on each item (various rules - Sometimes every item will be available for roll by all players sometimes once you get one item you are out - depends on amount of players and loot ussually first loot on droppable takes you out of the rest of the droppables)<br>
* peeps sign up for the item they want to roll for and then they are assigned numbers [1 thru 8 and then the RL can random 1 8 and then whom ever had that number gets the loot (Faddo / Neul's way)]<br>
<br>
Our raids have not been about money gain for players thus Droppable are generally about NBG - A perfect example would be When the Helm dropped in UP - we could have done an all roll on it and a non melee coulda sold that helm for between 10 and 15k (or more). But we offered it to just the warriors to roll on even tho (I think) it was actually cleric usable as well. That was a call I made as RL. I offered to let the clerics roll on the no drop bracer but they declined<br>
<br>
When I ML pick up raids or groupings - I hand out all sub 10 plat items as they drop in a circuit thru all players present - In Acrylia Caverns I hand out all droped weaps in a cycle and when I get the same amount of acrylia bricks as there are players I hand 1 out per. I split all stacked runes at Raids end or when peeps leave I give them a share.  There are LOTS of ways to ML - there is also the opportunity to have the ML sell all the stuff to merchant and split cash... depends on the loot table.<br>
<br>
our track record on plat split has been pretty poor - but I try to do this right if we are in a zone where plat drops (rare)<br>
<br>
