<br>
There is a lvl limit on raids for a reason ppl. If you are below the lvl limit and decide that you still want to join a raid, great, consider your reward raiding experience, you should not expect loot until all others of the appropriate lvl for the raid have a better item than what may drop, period.<br>
<br>
The above applies only to guild specific raids of course, as we cannot determine for other guilds what the loot rules should be for joint raids, for fairness a different system needs to be devised.<br>
<br>
To qualify my first statement in the post (since I did mention main puller as a make or break person, and that person usually being a monk), for our guild I consider Kunglao a much better dungeon puller than myself, therefore I do not fit into the make or break catagory, and expect nothing, but will be at every raid possible.<br>
<br>
I here NBG thrown around a lot, but don't think that roll if you can use truly accomplishes this.<br>
<br>
Some may agree, some may strongly disagree. All opinions are welcome, I have thick skin =).<br>
